ces centers the ambitious agendas of the school's four centers in entrepreneurship global management leadership and social innovation support the gsb's teaching research and community engagement efforts they also dramatically shape the student experience through innovative programs that support our curricular innovations knight management center state of the art facilities are designed to support the school's curriculum deepen multidisciplinary partnerships throughout the university and leverage the school's intimate scale and collaborative culture to create truly transformational educational experiences alumni are our lifeblood as part of the gsb community give others the life changing experience that shaped you help us keep the school at the forefront of management education as we change lives change organizations and change the world stanford business school alumni association admissions faculty & research alumni recruiters & companies giving executive education news about the gsb copyright 2012 stanford graduate school of business site help terms of use & policies stanford university
